<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="74" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Pacheco</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>,<lb/><date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-11"><hi rend="italic">September 11,
                            1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Wharton asks to be informed by telegraph of the penalty imposed by the
                        law of Salvador on a vessel leaving a port without clearance papers.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>